member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident

member.name: C:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident
member.remarks: If you want a constructor that assigns Value at the same time use the other constructor.

member.name: C:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident(System.String)
member.summary: Constructs a new Ident given the string 'value'.
member.remarks: Assigns a value to the 'Value' field during initalisation. If this string is not available at construct time use the other constructor and set 'Value' manually.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.ArrLoc
member.summary: Holds an expression that evaluates to the array location to load or store into.
member.remarks: This may be just the letter 'l' as an Ident so as to signal that the array length is required.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.Conv
member.summary: This flag must be set if a conversion is desired.
member.remarks: The TTok field must be set if this is set.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.DoNeg
member.summary: If a negation is wished this flag is to be set.
member.remarks: Set this only on identifiers that lead to numbers.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.DoNot
member.summary: If a biwise not is required set this flag.
member.remarks: Set this only on identifiers that point to boolean values.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.IsArr
member.summary: This flag must be set to perform an array access.
member.remarks: The slot to be used is to be put in ArrLoc.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.IsRef
member.summary: Set this flag to return the address of the memory location holding this identifier.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.IsValInRef
member.summary: If this identifer leads to an address and you wish to access the location at that address set this flag.
member.remarks: Such an identifier cannot be stored in fields.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.MemberAccessFlg
member.summary: This flag when set indicates method chaining behaviour.
member.remarks: If this is set, also set MemberToAccess to indicate the member of teh return type to chain into.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.MemberToAccess
member.summary: Indicates the member to access during method chaining.
member.remarks: Chaining only happens if MemberAccessFlg is set to true.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.OrdOp
member.summary: Indicates the order in which the unary operators get applied in.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ident.TTok
member.summary: Holds a type token indicating the type to convert to.
member.remarks: For a conversion to happen the Conv flag must be set to true.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.ImportTok

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.IncludeTok
member.remarks: This is used by the parser to detect a #include directive.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.LocimportTok
member.summary: Represents the soon to be deprecated 'locimport' keyword.
member.remarks: This class is used by the parser the soon to be deprecated local namespace import.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.MethodCallTok
member.summary: Represents a method call in the form method-name(param1,param2,...).
member.remarks: This class' design allows dylan.NET method calls to use method calls and expressions as parameters.

member.name: C:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.MethodCallTok(System.String)

member.param: The Expr instance holding the expression whose evaluated value will be passed as the parameter.

member.remarks: Initially the amount of parameters is 0.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.MethodCallTok.Name
member.summary: The MethodName instance containg the method's name and other information.
member.remarks: Any identifier whose Value is a valid and accessible method name can be used as a valid value for this field provided that the Params fields is adequatley set.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.MethodCallTok.Params
member.summary: The array of parameter expressions to be passed to the method.
member.remarks: The result type of each parameter in conjunction with the method name leads to the resolution of a MethodInfo instance.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.MethodNameTok
member.summary: Represents a method name i.e. the full string of characters before the '('.
member.remarks: This class inherits Ident and hence allows nearly all identifier operations like chaining and conversions to be made in the same way.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.MethodTok
member.remarks: This class is used by the parser to detect a method declaration.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.NullTok

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.OffTok

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.OnTok

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.RefasmTok

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.SwitchTok
member.summary: Represents an on/off option of a preprocessor directive which turns on/off a code generation feature.
member.remarks: The OnTok and OffTok classes inherit from this one and other ones may do so in order to support partial turning on of a feature.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token
member.summary: This is the Token class which is the basis for all of the dylan.NET AST.
member.remarks: All Tokens must directly or indirectly inherit from this class.

member.name: C:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token

member.name: C:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token(System.String)
member.param: The textual value of the Token to initialise.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token.Line
member.summary: The Line where this Token was found.
member.remarks: This is important for debug info emission.

member.name: M:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token.ToString
member.summary: Outputs the Token in terms of dylan.NET syntax.
member.returns: The dylan.NET syntax that represents this Token.
member.remarks: This method is overloaded in many subclasses as this implementation is too general.

member.name: F:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Token.Value
member.summary: The textual value of the Token.
member.remarks: From this the Parser module can further optimize the Token into other subclasses.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.VarTok
member.remarks: This class is used by the parser to detect a varible/parameter delaration.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.VerTok
member.remarks: This class is used by the parser to detect a version declaration.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.AbstractAttr
member.remarks: Only applicable to classes. Renders them abstract.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.AnsiClassAttr
member.remarks: May only be applied to classes. Forces the encoding used to ANSI.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.Attribute
member.summary: Represents a dylan.NET method, type, field or property attribute.
member.remarks: All such attributes must inherit from this class.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.AutoClassAttr
member.remarks: May only be applied to classes. Forces on them an automatic encoding.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.AutoLayoutAttr
member.remarks: May only be applied to classes. Allows the CLR to arrange their fields automatically.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.BeforeFieldInitAttr
member.remarks: May only be applied to classes. Forces the CLR to call their static constructors only once not on every use of the class. Has special use in static classes with static fields.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.PrivateAttr
member.remarks: Renders all members to which they are applied accessible ony inside the class that declares them.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.PublicAttr
member.remarks: Renders all members it is applied to fully accessible from every method in every class.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.SequentialLayoutAttr
member.remarks: May only be applied to classes. Forces the CLR to lay their fields in the same order they were defined in. Has special uses in defining structs used for P/Invoke purposes.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.SpecialNameAttr
member.remarks: May ony be applied to methods. Makes the CLR interpret their name as special. Useful in defining property accessors/getters and operator overloads.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Attributes.StaticAttr
member.remarks: May only be applied to methods. Renders them static as in not requiring an instance of the declaring class (no this pointer will be available in them).

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Chars.Ampersand

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Chars.Comma

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Chars.Cr

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Chars.RParen

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Chars.RSParen

member.remarks: This is used by the Parser to detect array accesses.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.AndOp
member.remarks: Does a bitwise and of its operands.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.AritOp
member.remarks: All arithmetic operators are required to inherit from this class.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.AssignOp
member.remarks: It is only allowed once in a statement and signals that the current Stmt is an AssignStmt.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.ConditionalOp
member.remarks: All conditional operators are required to inherit from this class.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.DecOp
member.remarks: Decrements its operator. Instances of DecOp are shortlived since they are translated to a flag inside the operand.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.EqOp
member.remarks: Checks if its operands are equal in value.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.GeOp
member.summary: Represents a greater or equal '>=' operator.
member.remarks: Checks if RChild is greather than or equal than LChild.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.GtOp
member.remarks: Checks if LChild is greaterr than RChild.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.IncOp
member.remarks: Increments its operand. Instances of IncOp are shortlived since they are translated into a flag inside the operand.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.LeOp
member.summary: Represents a less than or equal '<=' operator.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.LikeOp
member.remarks: Checks if the string LChild conforms to the pattern string RCHild. The library System.dll is required for its Regex components. Regex is being used instead of the VB Like operator as of 11.2.7.6.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.LogicalOp
member.remarks: All logical operators must be derived from this class.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.LtOp
member.remarks: Checks if LChild is less than RChild.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.ModOp
member.remarks: Calculates the remainder left when dividing LChild by RChild.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.NandOp
member.remarks: Does a bitwise and of its operators then negates the result.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.NegOp
member.summary: Represents a two's complement negation '!' operator.
member.remarks: Negates its operand. For signed number operands only. Equivalent to operand * -1. Instances of this class are shortlived since they are translated to a flag inside the operand.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.NeqOp
member.summary: Represents a not equal to '!=' operator.
member.remarks: Checks if the operators are non-equal in value.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.NLikeOp
member.summary: Represents a negated Regex Matching '!like' operator.
member.remarks: Checks if the string LChild is non-conformant to the pattern string RChild. The ibrary System.dll is required for its Regex components. REgex has been used instead of the VB like operator since 11.2.7.6.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.NorOp

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.NotOp

member.remarks: Does a one's complement bitwise not of its operand. Use only on boolean values. Instances of this class are shortlived since they are translated to a flag inside the operand.

member.name: T:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.Op

member.name: C:dylan.NET.Tokenizer.AST.Tokens.Ops.Op
member.remarks: Normally one would not want to construct an Op but one of its subclasses. This class is only useful for Op detection in general.
